msgid "[[!toc levels=3]]\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"This page is designed to give you quick howtos to flash common devices. It "
"is not meant to be a complete directory of all esoteric devices, others have "
"done this better."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#, no-wrap
msgid "Firmware downloads"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "OpenWRT firmware"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"To choose the firmware, look into the [table of "
"hardware](http://wiki.openwrt.org/toh/start) on the OpenWRT site, each "
"device page will list which firmware you should use."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "(!) Hint: most Linksys WRT54 devices use the brcm47xx firmware."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#, no-wrap
msgid "Flashing methods"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Web interface"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"If your router is still functional, the easiest way is to flash the device "
"through the web interface. This works on most firmware, even the proprietary "
"ones shipped with the device."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "During the upload, pay attention to the following:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "do not disconnect the network cable"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "do not close your browser"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "look at the LEDs pattern to see if they settle down"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
msgid "keep a ping to the router running"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "TFTP upload"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"(!) In general, use the [[!debpkg atftp]] package instead of plain "
"\"netkit\" tftp, as it is more reliable."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid "connect the router with a wire to your computer"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
msgid "configure an IP on your computer"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#:  
#, no-wrap
msgid "        ifconfig eth0:flash 192.168.1.2\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
msgid ""
"reboot the router with the reset button pressed until the leds flash like a "
"christmas tree"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '4. '
msgid "send the new firmware through tftp:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"        $ tftp 192.168.1.20\n"
"        tftp> binary\n"
"        tftp> put openwrt.bin\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "See also <http://wiki.openwrt.org/doc/howto/generic.flashing.tftp>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title #
#, no-wrap
msgid "Password reset"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"In general, try to connect on the web interface at <http://192.168.1.1> (a "
"commonly used default IP), that may give you an idea of the firmware that is "
"running."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "OpenWRT firmwares"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"If you are lucky enough to have a [[OpenWRT]] device, you may be able to "
"reset the password using this simpler procedure:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '1. '
msgid "Unplug the router's power cord."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '2. '
msgid "Connect the router's LAN1 port directly to your PC."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '3. '
msgid "Configure your PC with a static IP address"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '4. '
msgid "Plug the power on and wait for the DMZ LED to light up."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '5. '
msgid ""
"While the DMZ LED is on immediately press any button (Reset and Secure Easy "
"Setup will work) a few times ."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "If done right the DMZ LED will quickly flash 3 times every second."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"You should be able to telnet to the router at 192.168.1.1 now (no username "
"and password)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#, no-wrap
msgid "Simple tips to recover the router in failsafe mode"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"NOTE: The root file system in failsafe mode is the SquashFS partition "
"mounted in readonly mode. To switch to the normal writable root file system "
"run mount_root and make any changes. Run `mount_root` now."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Forgot/lost your password and you like to set a new one"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    passwd\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "Forgot the routers IP address"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    uci get network.lan.ipaddr\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"You accidentally run 'ipkg upgrade' or filled up the flash by installing to "
"big packages (clean the JFFS2 partition and start over)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "    mtd -r erase rootfs_data\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"If you are done with failsafe mode power cycle the router and boot in normal "
"mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#, no-wrap
msgid "Tomato firmware"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Just hold the reset key down until the power led flashes, see "
"<http://www.polarcloud.com/tomatofaq#why_doesnt_my_password_work>."
msgstr ""

